WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.720
Hi, my name is Sebastian and here are the top three things that you will get out of

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:10.720
this workshop.

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:15.400
So first, I will teach you about machine learning with Scikit-Learn and then I will introduce

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:18.139
PyTorch for deep learning.

00:00:18.139 --> 00:00:22.020
Both Scikit-Learn and PyTorch are the most widely used machine learning and deep learning

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:25.280
libraries out there in both academia and industry.

00:00:25.280 --> 00:00:29.740
So you get exposure to the most popular open source libraries for both machine learning

00:00:29.740 --> 00:00:31.100
and deep learning.

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:34.900
Second, you will learn to use these tools in a professional manner.

00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:39.180
I have experience in both teaching machine learning and deep learning classes in a statistics

00:00:39.180 --> 00:00:43.980
department and teaching deep learning and machine learning in industry contexts.

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:49.139
So I will combine these two strengths where we cover both the best practices for code

00:00:49.139 --> 00:00:52.500
implementations, but then also do this rigorously.

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:58.180
Third, I will also expose you to the cutting edge tools that are currently being used.

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:02.119
For instance, you are probably all familiar with large language models.

00:01:02.119 --> 00:01:07.139
So in this course, we will also learn how we tune and how we use large language models

00:01:07.139 --> 00:01:11.820
ourselves, which will give you access to the most latest machine learning models out there.

